Per‑Mode Nano64 Sprite/Palette Compensation
Composite video distorts color and edges.
Nano64’s 16‑color palette can be compensated per mode to preserve clarity.

NTSC Compensation
nano.palette.u_shift = +2
nano.palette.v_shift = -1
nano.sprite.edge_soften = 0.15
nano.sprite.dither = 0.10
nano.palette.saturation = 0.90

Reason: NTSC hue drift → slight UV correction

NTSC‑J Compensation

nano.palette.u_shift = +1
nano.palette.v_shift = -1
nano.sprite.edge_soften = 0.10
nano.palette.saturation = 1.00

PAL Compensation

nano.palette.u_shift = 0
nano.palette.v_shift = 0
nano.palette.saturation = 0.85
nano.sprite.edge_soften = 0.20
nano.sprite.dither = 0.15
Reason: PAL alternation stabilizes hue but reduces saturation

PAL60 Compensation

nano.palette.saturation = 0.90
nano.sprite.edge_soften = 0.15
SECAM Compensation
Code
nano.palette.saturation = 0.75
nano.palette.u_shift = 0
nano.palette.v_shift = 0
nano.sprite.edge_soften = 0.25
nano.sprite.dither = 0.20
Reason: SECAM FM chroma → stable but low saturation
